channel.title: Uh, Error Compiling, but I Haven't even touched the source codes
channel.description:
Well, I'm using the cheezscape source, and when I try Running my server, this comes up; [code]starting cheezscape server on 0.0.0.0:43594 config/objects.cfg:file not found. Summoning: Loading monsters from summon.cfg ... Summoning: Loaded 25 monsters from summon.cfg![/code] And it just stays like that, and when I try to compile, I get this error, [code]client.java:5147: unreachable statement if(item == 4708 && playerLevel[13] >= 85) ^ Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 1 error Press any key to continue . . .[/code] But... Like I said in the title, I didn't edit the server source in anyway as of yet. And by the way I'm using Zandia's Compiler, I was using Mopar's, But it kept saying that it didn't recognize JDK but I did set the paths.
I was wonder if Anyone could help me fix this Error?

When I compile it says;Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. Press any key to continue . . .
I read somewhere that means that the server is working, but I have no idea what to do now -.- I Hate feeling nooby and asking all these questions, But Ah well.
